  "prompt": "How can one use Bootstrap?",
  "response": "To use Bootstrap, follow these steps:\n\n1. Include Bootstrap in your project:\n\nOption 1: Using CDN (Quickest method)\n```html\n<!-- In the <head> section -->\n<link href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/css/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n\n<!-- Before closing </body> tag -->\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n```\n\nOption 2: Download and link locally\n```html\n<link href=\"path/to/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n<script src=\"path/to/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n```\n\nOption 3: Using npm (for advanced projects)\n```bash\nnpm install bootstrap\n```\n\n2. Basic HTML structure:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n    <link href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/css/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <title>Bootstrap Example</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <!-- Your content here -->\n\n    <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n3. Example of using Bootstrap classes:\n```html\n<!-- Container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n    <!-- Grid system -->\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-6\">Column 1</div>\n        <div class=\"col-md-6\">Column 2</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Button -->\n    <button class=\"btn btn-primary\">Click me</button>\n\n    <!-- Card -->\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"width: 18rem;\">\n        <div class=\"card-body\">\n            <h5 class=\"card-title\">Card Title</h5>\n            <p class=\"card-text\">Some quick example text.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n4. Responsive utilities:\n```html\n<!-- Responsive display -->\n<div class=\"d-none d-md-block\">Visible only on medium and larger screens</div>\n\n<!-- Spacing utilities -->\n<div class=\"m-3 p-2\">Margin and padding</div>\n\n<!-- Color utilities -->\n<div class=\"bg-primary text-white\">Colored background</div>\n```\n\n5. Using Bootstrap components:\n```html\n<!-- Dropdown -->\n<div class=\"dropdown\">\n    <button class=\"btn btn-secondary dropdown-toggle\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"dropdown\">\n        Dropdown\n    </button>\n    <ul class=\"dropdown-menu\">\n        <li><a class=\"dropdown-item\" href=\"#\">Action</a></li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n\n<!-- Modal -->\n<button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" data-bs-toggle=\"modal\" data-bs-target=\"#exampleModal\">\n    Launch modal\n</button>\n\n<div class=\"modal\" id=\"exampleModal\">\n    <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n        <div class=\"modal-content\">\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\n                <h5 class=\"modal-title\">Modal title</h5>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\n                Modal content\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nKey Tips:\n- Use the responsive grid system\n- Leverage utility classes\n- Check the official Bootstrap documentation\n- Customize with your own CSS as needed\n\nRecommended Resources:\n- Official Documentation: https://getbootstrap.com/docs/\n- Bootstrap Examples: https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/examples/\n\nRemember to always include the viewport meta tag for proper responsive behavior, and include both the CSS and JS files for full functionality of interactive components.",
